Name: FInputModeGameAndUI
Description: Data structure used to setup an input mode that allows the UI to respond to user input, and if the UI doesn't handle it player input / player controller gets a chance.

Name: FScalableFloat
Description: Generic numerical value in the form Value * Curve[Level]

Name: TEXT
Description: In Unreal Engine, string literals need to be wrapped with the TEXT macro to ensure cross-platform compatibility.

Name: UBlueprintAsyncActionBase
Description: Allows you to create asynchronous Blueprint nodes. These nodes can perform operations that don't block the main thread, such as networking tasks, file I/O, or waiting for a specific event.

Name: ULocalPlayer
Description: Each player that is active on the current client/listen server has a LocalPlayer
